  "statement": "The three roots $r_1, r_2, r_3$ of a cubic polynomial equation\n$x^3 + ax^2 + bx + c = 0$ are given by $$\\begin{aligned}\nr_1 & = & -\\frac{a}{3} + \\left(\\frac{-2a^3 + 9ab - 27c + \\sqrt{(2a^3-9ab+27c)^2 + 4(-a^2+3b)^3}}{54}\\right)^{1/3} \\\\\n& & {} + \\left(\\frac{-2a^3 + 9ab - 27c - \\sqrt{(2a^3-9ab+27c)^2 + 4(-a^2+3b)^3}}{54}\\right)^{1/3} \\\\\nr_2 & = & -\\frac{a}{3} - \\frac{1+i\\sqrt{3}}{2} \\left(\\frac{-2a^3 + 9ab - 27c + \\sqrt{(2a^3-9ab+27c)^2 + 4(-a^2+3b)^3}}{54}\\right)^{1/3} \\\\\n& & {} + \\frac{-1+i\\sqrt{3}}{2} \\left(\\frac{-2a^3 + 9ab - 27c - \\sqrt{(2a^3-9ab+27c)^2 + 4(-a^2+3b)^3}}{54}\\right)^{1/3} \\\\\nr_3 & = & -\\frac{a}{3} + \\frac{-1+i\\sqrt{3}}{2} \\left(\\frac{-2a^3 + 9ab - 27c + \\sqrt{(2a^3-9ab+27c)^2 + 4(-a^2+3b)^3}}{54}\\right)^{1/3} \\\\\n& & {} - \\frac{1+i\\sqrt{3}}{2} \\left(\\frac{-2a^3 + 9ab - 27c - \\sqrt{(2a^3-9ab+27c)^2 + 4(-a^2+3b)^3}}{54}\\right)^{1/3}\\end{aligned}$$",
